{"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"PWMOut","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"s:7SwiftIO6PWMOutC","roleHeading":"Class","role":"symbol","title":"PWMOut","symbolKind":"class","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"PWMOut"}],"modules":[{"name":"SwiftIO"}]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftIO\/documentation\/SwiftIO\/PWMOut"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftIO\/documentation\/SwiftIO"]]},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"final"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PWMOut"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A PWM signal switches rapidly between on and off. The longer the output stays","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"high, the higher the average voltage. There are two key factors: the frequency"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and duty cycle. "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Frequency"}]},{"text":" defines the speed of on-off switching.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Duty cycle"}]},{"type":"text","text":" decides the proportion of high output in a period."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To start with, you need to initialize a pin as a PWMOut pin. A physical pin"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"may be connected to various internal peripherals and thus serve multiple"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"functionalities. You need to identify the specific pin using its id and specify"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the pin’s functionality before using it."}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"PWMOut","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" tells the pin’s usage.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"Id.PWM0A","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" defines which pin is used. You may refer to the board’s pinout","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"which shows all pins and their corresponding functions in a diagram."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let pin = PWMOut(Id.PWM0A)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can also set the default frequency and duty cycle of the PWM pin when","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"initializing it.","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let pin = PWMOut(Id.PWM0A, frequency: 1500, dutycycle: 0.5)"]},{"name":"Important","style":"important","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The PWM pins with same number are paired, like PWM3A and PWM3B.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"They can only share the same frequency."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"anchor":"Example-1-Light-a-LED-with-a-specified-brightness","type":"heading","text":"Example 1: Light a LED with a specified brightness","level":3},{"code":["\/\/ Import the SwiftIO to use the related board functions.","import SwiftIO","\/\/ Import the MadBoard to decide which pin is used for the specific function.","import MadBoard","","\/\/ Initialize a PWMOut pin PWM0A with default setting.","let led = PWMOut(Id.PWM0A)","","\/\/ Setting the duty cycle to light the LED with half brightness.","led.setDutycycle(0.5)","","while true {","   sleep(ms: 1000)","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In this case, the duty cycle of PWM output affects the LED brightness, since it","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"sets the proportion of the LED on time during a period. The frequency of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the signal only changes how fast the LED turns on and off. As long as it is not"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"too low, the flicker will be unnoticeable.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Example-2-Make-sound-with-a-buzzer","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Example 2: Make sound with a buzzer"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["import SwiftIO","import MadBoard","","let buzzer = PWMOut(Id.PWM0A, frequency: 0)","","\/\/ Set the frequency of PWM to decide the sound pitch.","\/\/ The duty cycle can be any value bigger than 0 to generate sound.","buzzer.set(frequency: 1500, dutycycle: 0.5)","\/\/ Keep the sound for 1s.","sleep(ms: 1000)","\/\/ Suspend the PWM output to stop the sound.","buzzer.suspend()","","while true {","   sleep(ms: 1000)","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In this example, the sound from a buzzer relates to the movement of its internal","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"component. The faster the movement, the higher the pitch. So the frequency plays","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"an important role.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftio\/pwmout"]}],"abstract":[{"text":"The PWMOut class is used to generate periodic square waves and modulate the pulse","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"width to get different average output."}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Initializer","anchor":"Initializer","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftIO\/documentation\/SwiftIO\/PWMOut\/init(_:frequency:dutycycle:)"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftIO\/documentation\/SwiftIO\/PWMOut\/set(frequency:dutycycle:)","doc:\/\/SwiftIO\/documentation\/SwiftIO\/PWMOut\/set(period:pulse:)","doc:\/\/SwiftIO\/documentation\/SwiftIO\/PWMOut\/setDutycycle(_:)","doc:\/\/SwiftIO\/documentation\/SwiftIO\/PWMOut\/suspend()","doc:\/\/SwiftIO\/documentation\/SwiftIO\/PWMOut\/resume()"],"anchor":"Setting-PWM","title":"Setting PWM"},{"generated":true,"title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftIO\/documentation\/SwiftIO\/PWMOut\/maxFrequency","doc:\/\/SwiftIO\/documentation\/SwiftIO\/PWMOut\/minFrequency"],"anchor":"Instance-Properties"}],"references":{"doc://SwiftIO/documentation/SwiftIO/PWMOut":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"PWMOut","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PWMOut"}],"title":"PWMOut","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftIO\/documentation\/SwiftIO\/PWMOut","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The PWMOut class is used to generate periodic square waves and modulate the pulse"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"width to get different average output.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swiftio\/pwmout","kind":"symbol"},"doc://SwiftIO/documentation/SwiftIO/PWMOut/suspend()":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Suspends the PWM output."}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swiftio\/pwmout\/suspend()","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"suspend","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}],"title":"suspend()","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftIO\/documentation\/SwiftIO\/PWMOut\/suspend()"},"doc://SwiftIO/documentation/SwiftIO":{"title":"SwiftIO","role":"collection","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftIO\/documentation\/SwiftIO","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The SwiftIO library allows you to access and control the hardware in an easy way."}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swiftio"},"doc://SwiftIO/documentation/SwiftIO/PWMOut/setDutycycle(_:)":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets the percentage of time during a period in which the output is high,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"from 0.0 to 